==Demographics==
As of the 2020 United States census, there were 191 people living in Brandy Station.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Brandy Station CDP, Virginia|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/profile?g=1600000US5109352|publisher=United States Census Bureau|access-date=October 4, 2025}}</ref> The racial makeup of the CDP was 62.8% White, 18.3% Black or African American, 14.1% from other races, and 3.7% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 15.7% of the population.<ref>{{cite web|title=Brandy Station CDP, Virginia Population By Race and Ethnicity 2020|url=https://beautifydata.com/united-states-population/census/2020/population-by-race-and-ethnicity-per-city-or-place/virginia/brandy-station-cdp|publisher=BeautifyData (U.S. Census data)|access-date=October 4, 2025}}</ref>  

Of the population, 29.8% were under the age of 18, 56.0% were between 18 and 64, and 14.1% were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 35.8 years.<ref>{{cite web|title=CityPopulation – Brandy Station (Culpeper, Virginia)|url=https://www.citypopulation.de/en/usa/places/virginia/culpeper/5109352__brandy_station/|publisher=CityPopulation.de|access-date=October 4, 2025}}</ref>  

According to the American Community Survey, the estimated per capita income was $33,881, and about 16.7% of residents were below the poverty line.<ref>{{cite web|title=Brandy Station, Virginia profile|url=https://censusreporter.org/profiles/16000US5109352-brandy-station-va/|publisher=Census Reporter|access-date=October 4, 2025}}</ref>
